The article discusses the proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump designating May 7, 2020, as a National Day of Prayer in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the country's historical reliance on prayer during challenging times, such as the Revolutionary War, the Civil War, and World Wars, as well as the current coronavirus pandemic. It calls for Americans to come together and pray for healing, strength, and guidance. The proclamation also encourages observing the day with appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities in various settings, while following the White House's guidelines for reopening the country.